Which ADT would you end up choosing for solving this problem? Why?
The map ADT should be chosen.

Why:

The vector + set solution requires nested loops, resulting in an O(RV) runtime for finding the most voted restaurant.

The map-based solution stores vote counts as data is read, eliminating the need for repeated counting.

The overall runtime using maps is:

O(Vlog⁡R)+O(R)
O(VlogR)+O(R)

which is significantly more efficient than the vector-based approach.

Maps are a better fit because the problem naturally involves associating restaurants with vote counts.
